# Cursor Rules for Moombs Project

## Odoo Compliance
glob: **/*.py
description: Ensure Odoo coding standards and best practices are followed
rules:
  - All Python files should have proper docstrings following Odoo standards
  - Use snake_case for method and variable names
  - Class names should use CamelCase
  - Model names should be lowercase with underscores
  - Field names should be lowercase with underscores
  - Security rules must be defined for all models
  - Use proper Odoo decorators (@api.model, @api.depends, etc.)
  - Follow Odoo's ORM methods instead of raw SQL
  - Include proper license headers in module files
  - Use translation markers (_) for user-facing strings
  - Follow Odoo's module structure:
    - __init__.py
    - __manifest__.py
    - models/
    - views/
    - security/
    - data/
  - Use proper version numbers in manifest
  - Define dependencies correctly in manifest
  - Use proper XML IDs for views and data
  - Follow Odoo's view inheritance patterns
  - Use proper field attributes (required, readonly, states, etc.)
  - Implement proper access rights and record rules
  - Use proper import statements
  - Follow PEP 8 guidelines with Odoo exceptions

## API Development
glob: **/api/**/*.py
description: Guidelines for API development
rules:
  - Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
  - Implement proper error handling
  - Use proper status codes
  - Document all endpoints
  - Implement proper validation
  - Use proper security measures
  - Follow RESTful principles
  - Implement proper rate limiting
  - Use proper versioning
  - Implement proper logging